						<summary>

						<p>At the entrance into the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> in front of the central shrine of the Ratnāchalēśvara temple, left side.</p>						

						<p>c. 12th Century.</p>						

						<p>States that a certain Maṟaikalandāṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Koṅgarai-koṇḍa-Pallavaraiyaṉ, one of the <hi rend="italic">agampaḍi-mudalis</hi> of Chāttan Chēdirāyaṉ, built the entrance steps and fixed the door to this <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> and built the <hi rend="italic">tirumaḍai-viḷāgam</hi> (temple streets) at the foot of the hill and settled them with people.</p>						

						</summary>
